---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Documentation">
	<section class="py-12">
		<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 tracking-tight">Introduction</h1>
		<p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 mb-8 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
			HayUi is a premium React component library built with Tailwind CSS. It focuses on clean aesthetics, soft colors, and smooth interactions using the Satoshi font.
		</p>

		<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-12">
			<div class="p-6 bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
				<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Modern Aesthetics</h3>
				<p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Soft color palettes and refined typography for a professional look and feel.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="p-6 bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
				<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Fully Accessible</h3>
				<p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Built with accessibility in mind, following WAI-ARIA best practices.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="p-6 bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
				<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Highly Customizable</h3>
				<p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Easily theme and extend components using simple Tailwind CSS utilities.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="p-6 bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
				<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Lightweight</h3>
				<p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Optimized for performance with minimal runtime overhead.</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="mt-16">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Quick Start</h2>
			<div class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg p-6 overflow-x-auto">
				<pre class="text-blue-400"><code>npm install hayui</code></pre>
				<pre class="text-neutral-400 mt-2"><code>// Add to your project
import &#123; Ember &#125; from 'hayui';

function App() &#123;
  return &lt;Ember variant="primary"&gt;Get Started&lt;/Ember&gt;;
&#125;</code></pre>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
